    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-12T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-12T20:00:00-05:00" n="741"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.67/11–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-13T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 13, 1948—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 13—1:25 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2198. Reur 669.<note n="42a" xml:id="d741fn42a">Same as telegram No. 536,
                        November 9, 9 a. m., from the Consul General at Mukden, <ref
                            target="#pg_829">p. 829</ref>.</note> Since closing of Vladivostok
                    Consulate we have been unable to get courier to Dairen;<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d741fn43">For correspondence concerning Dairen, see <ref
                            target="#pg_787">pp. 787</ref> ff.</note> therefore, urge that
                    arrangements for courier travel be not through Soviet controlled areas.</p>
                <p>Sent Mukden 193, repeated Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
